China's House Rent Price Index Slightly Up 
China's house rent price index rose slightly by 2.2 percent in the
third quarter of 2000, according to the latest figures from the
National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).
The rent for residential houses went up 6.6 percent, compared with the
same period of 1999.
Rent for hotels gained 1.9 percent, but rent for non-luxury hotels
dipped four percent.
Rent for high-class office buildings was 0.8 percent up, but rent for
standard office building was down 1.6 percent.
The rent for industrial and warehouse space slid 2.8 percent and 1.8
percent, respectively.
